Name: alpha 1-antitrypsin deficiency
Definition: A plasma protein metabolism disease that has_material_basis_in defective production of the protease inhibitor alpha 1-antitrypsin (A1AT)

Name: polyclonal hypergammaglobulinemia
Definition: A synostosis that results_in premature fusion located_in skull.

Name: monoclonal paraproteinemia
Definition: An inherited metabolic disorder that involves plasma protein metabolism malfunction.

Name: macroglobulinemia
Definition: A lupus erythematosus that is an inflammation of connective tissue marked by skin rashes

Name: obsolete mycosis fungoides involving intrathoracic lymph nodes
Definition: A lupus erythematosus that is an inflammation of connective tissue marked by skin rashes
Synonym: Mycosis fungoides of intrathoracic lymph nodes (disorder)

Name: obsolete Hodgkin's lymphoma
Definition: A lupus erythematosus that is an inflammation of connective tissue marked by skin rashes
